ChapterShortDescription: Developers Students Club COET is an initiative with the support of Google Developers Group to concentrate the efforts of many developers in COET to learn, share and get productive using the various Google products.
ChapterLongDec: Developers Students Club COET is inspired by GDG Family . We started our journey in Feb 2018. We try to engage student developers through our hack events & meetups. The motive is to create a local ecosystem of programmers & hackers in COET. The technology awareness is main goal for first few years of the group.
aboutGDGProgram: DSCs are local groups of developers who are specifically interested in Google products and APIs. Each local group is called a DSC chapter and can host a variety of technical activities for developers - from just a few people getting together to watch our latest videos, to large gatherings with demos and tech talks, to hackathons.
